WEBVTT

00:47.831 --> 00:51.831
www.titlovi.com

00:54.831 --> 00:56.298
Baby-sitters Club.

00:56.499 --> 00:58.330
This is Mrs. Rodowsky.

00:58.401 --> 01:02.565
Hi. We´re going out for dinner on Tuesday
with the whole family.

01:02.638 --> 01:05.630
l was wondering, would any of you mind
baby-sitting the dog?

01:05.708 --> 01:08.404
l mean, he just hates to be left alone.

01:42.712 --> 01:44.077
Baby-sitters Club.

01:44.914 --> 01:49.044
l´m on a car phone. l need a sitter
for tonight. lt´s an emergency.

01:50.820 --> 01:54.017
Hi, this is Mrs. Wilder.
l´m having a birthday party for Rosie...

01:54.090 --> 01:56.524
and do any of you dress up as clowns?

01:57.360 --> 01:58.850
Hi, l need a sitter tonight.

01:58.928 --> 02:02.056
My sister was gonna watch the kids,
but she flaked out.

02:02.665 --> 02:06.396
lt´s me again. My wife´s going
into the hospital any minute.

02:06.469 --> 02:08.994
We´re pregnant. No, l mean, she´s pregnant.

02:09.072 --> 02:11.870
Anyway, we´ve got a toddler at home and....

02:46.809 --> 02:48.003
Baby-sitters Club.

02:48.077 --> 02:50.568
We´re gonna need a baby-sitter
Saturday night.

02:50.646 --> 02:52.807
We need a baby-sitter on Friday night.

02:52.882 --> 02:56.079
l know it´s only August,
but could l book for New Year´s Eve?

02:56.152 --> 02:58.177
Yeah. lt´s me again. Listen.

02:58.254 --> 03:01.087
ls anyone, like, immediately....

03:47.370 --> 03:47.537
My name is Kristy. l´m the founding member
of the Baby-sitters Club.

03:47.537 --> 03:51.530
My name is Kristy. l´m the founding member
of the Baby-sitters Club.

03:51.774 --> 03:54.504
l don´t mean to brag,
but we´re famous here in Stoneybrook.

03:54.577 --> 03:55.601
Hey, Kristy!

03:55.678 --> 03:58.704
Everybody knows us.
That´s because everybody uses us.

03:59.148 --> 04:00.445
You call one number...

04:00.516 --> 04:03.576
and get connected
to seven incredible baby-sitters.

04:10.259 --> 04:12.989
This is Stacey. She´s our club treasurer.

04:13.062 --> 04:16.759
She´s good at keeping track of money.
She´s also good at spending it.

04:16.832 --> 04:20.632
Stace was raised in New York City.
Sometimes she thinks she still lives there.

04:20.702 --> 04:21.863
358 Bradford Court.

04:23.005 --> 04:24.097
That´s Mary Anne.

04:24.173 --> 04:26.971
When we were little,
we used to live next door to each other.

04:27.043 --> 04:29.238
She´s kind of quiet, kind of serious.

04:29.312 --> 04:32.304
Why are we friends?
They say opposites attract.

04:33.716 --> 04:35.513
Dawn is Mary Anne´s stepsister.

04:35.585 --> 04:37.450
She grew up in California.

04:37.520 --> 04:39.818
Dawn really cares about the environment.

04:39.889 --> 04:43.416
Her biggest regret is that
she wasn´t born on Earth Day.

04:44.694 --> 04:47.492
Claudia´s an amazing artist.
She´s really talented.

04:47.797 --> 04:52.097
Do you know anybody who could take a fork
and a hammer and turn it into that?

04:53.769 --> 04:57.102
And, of course, Mallory.
She´s a junior member of the club.

04:57.173 --> 04:58.970
She wants to be a writer.

04:59.041 --> 05:01.202
She started her novel when she turned 11...

05:01.277 --> 05:04.508
and is determined to finish it
by the time she´s eleven-and-a-half.

05:06.449 --> 05:08.417
Jessi is Mallory´s best friend.

05:08.484 --> 05:10.975
She´s 11, too, and our other junior member.

05:11.053 --> 05:13.920
Jessi´s motto is.:
´´Why walk when you can dance?´´

05:15.391 --> 05:18.053
You know, we´re more than just a club.

05:18.127 --> 05:20.755
We´re friends. Best friends.

05:20.830 --> 05:23.094
Nothing could ever change that.

05:25.635 --> 05:28.661
Dawn, l heard that Alan Gray likes you.

05:28.738 --> 05:31.366
Likes her, or ´´like´´ likes her?

05:31.440 --> 05:34.307
That dweeb? Spare me.
lt doesn´t matter anyway...

05:34.377 --> 05:37.175
because l don´t like him or ´´like´´ like him.

05:37.246 --> 05:40.238
Something´s wrong here, you guys.
School´s out, and l miss it.

05:40.316 --> 05:42.511
l know. lt´s not that l love it. lt´s just....

05:42.585 --> 05:46.419
-We don´t see each other every day?
-We end up baby-sitting at different houses.

05:46.489 --> 05:49.185
-We might as well be on separate planets.
-Yeah.

05:51.894 --> 05:55.728
The first Baby-sitters Club meeting
of the summer is now called to order.

05:55.798 --> 05:59.734
We have our meetings in Claudia´s room.
lt´s the best part of the week.

05:59.802 --> 06:02.566
We started there
because she´s the only one with a phone...

06:02.638 --> 06:04.265
but now it´s home.

06:04.340 --> 06:07.832
-Soy-meal chips? Forget it.
-They´re good for sugar addiction.

06:07.910 --> 06:10.504
l know l´m late,
but there was this really big--

06:10.579 --> 06:11.603
Sale!

06:11.681 --> 06:13.774
What´d you get this time?

06:14.417 --> 06:16.783
-You´re too much.
-Baby-sitters Club.

06:17.186 --> 06:18.619
Hi, Mrs. Rodowsky.

06:19.488 --> 06:22.286
Wednesday night, 6:00 to 9:30. Sure.

06:22.858 --> 06:25.383
-Got it. Hold on. Who´s free Wednesday?
-Not me.

06:25.461 --> 06:27.554
According to the schedule...

06:28.397 --> 06:30.092
you and me, but count me out.

06:30.166 --> 06:33.602
Last time it took me two hours
to get that dog clean.

06:34.270 --> 06:36.431
Okay, Mrs. Rodowsky, you´re all set.

06:36.505 --> 06:39.668
l´ll be there at 6:00 sharp. Okay, bye.

06:40.710 --> 06:44.612
l know Jackie Rodowsky´s
a walking disaster, but l like him, okay?

06:44.680 --> 06:46.910
-New business.
-We have a tragedy here.

06:46.982 --> 06:49.450
l flunked science
and l have to go to summer school.

06:49.518 --> 06:52.180
-Are your parents gonna kill you?
-Maybe.

06:52.254 --> 06:55.451
Don´t sweat it, Claud.
l got straight A´s in science this year.

06:55.524 --> 06:57.788
-l´ll coach you.
-Claud, you´re an artist.

06:57.860 --> 07:00.124
-You don´t have to be a scientist.
-She´s right.

07:00.196 --> 07:03.893
Tell that to my mom. lf l don´t get a C plus,
l have to drop out of the club.

07:04.266 --> 07:07.258
-Don´t worry. We´ll help you.
-You´ll pass. Promise.

07:07.470 --> 07:09.062
What if l don´t?

07:13.376 --> 07:15.003
Baby-sitters Club.

07:21.384 --> 07:23.147
Okay, l´ll tell her.

07:23.786 --> 07:27.722
Stace, that was Ms. Wilder. She says that
her little nephew´s coming in tonight.

07:27.790 --> 07:31.487
-He´s from Switzerland.
-Great. l love little kids with accents.

07:32.795 --> 07:33.989
Hello!

07:38.334 --> 07:41.428
-Hi, Stacey.
-Hi, Rosie. You´re getting so good.

07:41.504 --> 07:42.493
Thank you.

07:42.571 --> 07:46.029
l have a treat for you in the Kid Kit:
extra stickers and puzzles.

07:46.108 --> 07:47.097
Great.

07:47.610 --> 07:51.171
And l brought something
for your little cousin. Where is he?

07:51.247 --> 07:52.771
Hi, l´m Luca...

07:52.848 --> 07:54.509
the little cousin.

07:58.354 --> 07:59.981
You brought me a gift?

08:02.691 --> 08:06.354
lt´s just a small, little...

08:07.696 --> 08:09.994
American flag thing.

08:15.337 --> 08:17.703
Cool. Very nationalistic.

08:18.340 --> 08:19.830
And you´re....

08:20.409 --> 08:23.310
Stacey. Your sitter, l guess.

08:25.281 --> 08:27.977
l thought you were going to the movies.

08:28.350 --> 08:30.841
l have my whole life to go to the movies.

08:43.466 --> 08:45.161
Have you seen Karen and Andrew?

08:45.234 --> 08:47.702
Weren´t they
with David Michael and Emily Michelle?

08:47.770 --> 08:50.466
-This house is too big.
-Can l have my own phone?

08:50.539 --> 08:51.563
-Andrew!
-No.

08:51.640 --> 08:54.632
-But l need it for business.
-When you´re 16.

08:54.710 --> 08:58.305
-Kristy, have you seen Karen and Andrew?
-But this doesn´t make any sense.

08:58.380 --> 09:00.007
lt doesn´t have to.

09:00.115 --> 09:04.142
You won´t let me have BSC meetings here.
At least give me a phone.

09:04.220 --> 09:08.816
We live too far away to have them here,
and l don´t want you to have a phone.

09:08.891 --> 09:10.882
They´re not upstairs or in the garage.

09:10.960 --> 09:13.019
-You can´t just say no.
-Karen!

09:13.095 --> 09:15.859
A good parent would give their child
a logical reason.

09:15.931 --> 09:18.923
-l don´t want you to be spoiled.
-l´m already spoiled.

09:19.001 --> 09:20.434
They have to be somewhere.

09:20.503 --> 09:23.472
Where? They´re not upstairs.
They´re not under the beds.

09:23.539 --> 09:25.564
l looked under the beds. l looked under--

09:25.641 --> 09:26.733
l know.

09:26.809 --> 09:30.074
They´re with Colonel Mustard in the library
with the wrench.

09:32.781 --> 09:35.909
l´m Pirate Esmeralda, and this is my slave.

09:36.385 --> 09:38.819
What would you guys do without me?

09:39.922 --> 09:43.221
Thanks for helping me baby-sit.
Here´s half of what l made tonight.

09:43.292 --> 09:45.055
No, keep your money.

09:45.594 --> 09:48.290
You know,
l baby-sit Rosie every Wednesday.

09:48.364 --> 09:50.229
From 7:30 to 9:30.

09:50.299 --> 09:52.665
What about every other night of your life?

09:52.735 --> 09:55.898
-Do you like the movies?
-Mary Poppins is her favorite.

09:55.971 --> 09:58.462
We´ve seen that video 100,000 times.

09:58.807 --> 10:00.900
Well, l baby-sit her a lot.

10:03.812 --> 10:07.111
Why don´t you go out with me Saturday?
We could go to the movies.

10:07.182 --> 10:10.583
lf nothing is playing,
you could show me around Stoneybrook.

10:11.186 --> 10:12.915
This is kinda it.

10:12.988 --> 10:15.582
lt´s not like New York City or anything.

10:15.658 --> 10:18.354
That´s where l grew up.
Have you ever been there?

10:18.427 --> 10:21.089
-No, not yet.
-lt´s the best.

10:22.197 --> 10:23.687
You mean, like you?

10:26.535 --> 10:28.435
Are you gonna kiss her?

10:29.638 --> 10:32.266
Whatever gave you that idea, Rosalind?

10:32.808 --> 10:34.469
Come on, let´s go.

10:36.712 --> 10:39.977
-Don´t let them burn.
-Do you think l should have told him?

10:40.049 --> 10:41.880
-What? Who?
-Luca.

10:41.951 --> 10:43.714
He doesn´t know l have diabetes.

10:43.786 --> 10:47.620
lt´s not like you have the flu or something.
He can´t catch it.

10:47.690 --> 10:51.057
Yeah, l mean, if he´s any kind of guy,
he won´t care.

10:51.260 --> 10:53.694
l don´t want him to know.
He´ll think l´m pathetic.

10:53.762 --> 10:57.664
We all know. We don´t think you´re pathetic.
A little psycho maybe.

10:57.733 --> 10:59.598
He also doesn´t know l´m only 13.

10:59.668 --> 11:01.636
-So?
-He´s 1 7.

11:01.704 --> 11:04.070
-That´s ancient.
-He´s a poet.

11:04.139 --> 11:05.936
-He drives.
-He´s a musical genius.

11:06.008 --> 11:08.977
-He´s been to Europe.
-He´s from Europe.

11:10.312 --> 11:11.745
-Cough it up.
-Here´s mine.

11:11.814 --> 11:13.076
-Count me in.
-l forgot mine.

11:13.148 --> 11:14.775
Stace, treasurer´s report.

11:14.850 --> 11:16.784
After dues, we´ll have $58.

11:16.852 --> 11:19.412
But after the phone bill
and Kid Kit supplies...

11:19.488 --> 11:21.718
we´ll have $1 1 .47.

11:21.790 --> 11:23.257
-That´s all?
-We´re loaded.

11:23.325 --> 11:25.054
Okay, new business.

11:25.394 --> 11:27.157
l have a brilliant idea.

11:29.498 --> 11:31.625
Stoneybrook Summer Camp for Seniors?

11:31.700 --> 11:34.328
No! A day camp for our clients.

11:34.603 --> 11:38.300
lt´ll give us a new service to offer.
lt´ll be a total gold mine...

11:38.374 --> 11:41.935
and most important, it´s a way for us
to stay together the whole summer.

11:42.011 --> 11:44.571
ls this not the most brilliant idea yet?

11:48.050 --> 11:52.009
Last time she was like this,
she wanted us to open a dude ranch.

11:52.087 --> 11:55.989
No, seriously, you guys.
lt´ll be so easy, and the kids´ll love it.

11:56.058 --> 11:59.323
We can go from 10:00 to 4:00,
Monday through Friday or something.

11:59.395 --> 12:02.228
We can start after the Fourth of July,
give us time to set up.

12:02.297 --> 12:05.027
l don´t know what we´ll charge,
but we can figure that out.

12:05.100 --> 12:08.467
l´ve put together some start-up budgets
and schedules to check out.

12:08.537 --> 12:10.061
Here, you guys.

12:11.440 --> 12:13.772
-lt looks good, Kristy.
-You guys share.

12:14.343 --> 12:18.404
Kristy, this brilliant idea
might really be brilliant.

12:23.919 --> 12:26.752
My dad said we could use the yard,
but there are a few rules.

12:26.822 --> 12:28.551
The first, in bold print and underlined:

12:28.624 --> 12:31.184
-´´The house is off-limits to children.´´
-´´At all times.´´

12:31.260 --> 12:33.319
-How many pages are there?
-Don´t ask.

12:33.395 --> 12:36.023
Just our luck
your dad´s a lawyer, Mary Anne.

12:36.098 --> 12:37.861
Okay, let´s start marking it off.

12:37.933 --> 12:41.130
-Let´s put the sports area....
-Let´s put it over there.

12:41.203 --> 12:43.831
-The dance area over there.
-First-aid tent back there.

12:43.906 --> 12:47.342
-What about arts and crafts?
-We can line up Porta-Potties by the fence.

12:47.409 --> 12:49.570
Perfect. We´ll put the garbage cans
next to them.

12:49.645 --> 12:51.840
-Will the neighbors be a problem?
-They´re cool.

12:51.914 --> 12:54.314
-What about the new one?
-What about her?

12:54.516 --> 12:57.212
You guys, my dad needs us
to sign this contract...

12:57.286 --> 12:59.550
and initial all the pages he´s marked.

12:59.988 --> 13:02.718
-Put your John Hancock right there.
-This will be great.

13:02.791 --> 13:05.282
Shouldn´t we read this before we sign it?

13:14.737 --> 13:18.730
Jackie Rodowsky´s one of my best clients
and the first camper to sign up.

13:18.807 --> 13:21.105
His dream is to hit a home run.

13:21.243 --> 13:23.643
Problem is, he can´t even hit a ball.

13:23.712 --> 13:27.808
Too bad he doesn´t want to be a jockey,
because he can stay on a horse.

13:28.751 --> 13:31.083
Cokie Mason´s hated us
since the third grade.

13:31.153 --> 13:32.882
Everyone´s forgotten why.

13:32.955 --> 13:36.254
Her number-one mission in life
is to put the BSC out of business.

13:36.325 --> 13:38.384
Your helmet´s on backwards.

13:38.460 --> 13:40.587
Hurts my ears the other way.

13:45.334 --> 13:47.666
That´s Logan Bruno, Mary Anne´s boyfriend.

13:47.736 --> 13:50.204
He´s an associate member of the BSC.

13:50.272 --> 13:53.935
Mary Anne´s been in love with Logan
since he moved here from Kentucky.

13:54.009 --> 13:56.375
Unfortunately, so has Cokie Mason.

13:56.445 --> 13:59.505
Look at Kristy
and her band of goody two-shoes.

14:00.249 --> 14:03.548
What do they think they are?
One big, happy family?

14:04.219 --> 14:07.882
-Kristy, this horse won´t let me down.
-Hey, you all. How´s the ride?

14:07.956 --> 14:11.221
l´ll grab Logan´s arm
and you go distract Mary Anne, okay?

14:11.293 --> 14:12.851
What if she doesn´t leave him alone?

14:12.928 --> 14:16.295
Mary Anne and Logan
never let each other out of their sight.

14:16.365 --> 14:18.731
What are they afraid of? Moi?

14:21.236 --> 14:23.966
Logan, l´m so glad you´re here.

14:24.039 --> 14:26.473
-l wanted to call you.
-Oh, yeah?

14:26.542 --> 14:29.670
-Get lost, Cokie.
-Hello, Kristin.

14:30.279 --> 14:31.940
You have a date...

14:32.047 --> 14:36.381
and l can see his age is the same as your lQ.

14:36.718 --> 14:39.482
Who let you out
of that bat cave, Marguerite?

14:39.555 --> 14:41.614
She hates to be called that.

14:41.690 --> 14:43.555
That´s your real name?

14:44.026 --> 14:46.995
No. lt´s the mumbling of an idiot.

14:50.766 --> 14:52.131
Stall her.

14:54.203 --> 14:55.898
Go do what l said.

15:01.643 --> 15:03.110
l have to talk to you.

15:05.280 --> 15:06.645
Mary Anne?

15:09.184 --> 15:10.845
-Hi.
-Hi.

15:14.022 --> 15:15.114
Wait!

15:16.491 --> 15:19.324
What classes are you taking next year?

15:19.628 --> 15:22.222
l don´t really know yet. Why?

15:24.600 --> 15:26.898
Can l try on your riding pants?

15:28.937 --> 15:31.997
-Fifth row? Center? How´d you get them?
-Logan?

15:32.374 --> 15:34.239
l knew you´d say yes. Just think.

15:34.309 --> 15:36.470
You, me, and Smashing Pumpkins.

15:36.545 --> 15:38.604
-What are you doing?
-Cokie, l....

15:38.680 --> 15:40.147
-Cokie?
-What?

15:40.515 --> 15:43.279
-Don´t you have somewhere else to be?
-Don´t waste my time.

15:43.352 --> 15:45.320
Logan, call me tomorrow.

15:46.989 --> 15:49.082
Logan, l don´t believe you.

15:50.158 --> 15:51.819
Come on, let´s go.

16:36.071 --> 16:38.005
She´s eating seeds again.

16:38.073 --> 16:42.271
lsn´t it great how every time we come here
the burgers taste the same?

16:42.344 --> 16:45.575
l like that. Something you can count on.

16:45.647 --> 16:48.343
Dawn, have you watered yourself lately?

16:48.417 --> 16:49.543
What?

16:50.686 --> 16:53.951
Kristy, you got a birthday coming up.
What should we do?

16:54.022 --> 16:57.856
l don´t know. Just as long as
it´s the best day of my life. But no pressure.

16:57.926 --> 17:00.986
Guys, $250 per camper.

17:01.063 --> 17:04.863
lf 30 campers sign up, that´s $7,500.

17:05.901 --> 17:07.266
We´re rich.

17:07.336 --> 17:10.863
-We can almost buy a car.
-ln five years, we can drive it.

17:10.939 --> 17:13.601
lf we get enough money,
we can open our own office.

17:13.675 --> 17:16.337
-That´s a great idea.
-We could get a fax machine.

17:16.411 --> 17:19.847
-Go international.
-That´ll sure let me off the hook if l flunk.

17:19.915 --> 17:22.816
-You´re not gonna flunk.
-Claud, l´ll help you.

17:23.218 --> 17:24.207
Okay.

17:24.819 --> 17:26.310
l say we start looking.

17:26.387 --> 17:28.288
How many people have we signed up?

17:28.357 --> 17:30.325
On our last count, we had...

17:31.560 --> 17:32.754
twelve.

17:36.331 --> 17:38.526
We passed out a million fliers.

17:38.600 --> 17:42.161
-My brother David Michael will come.
-How´s your little day camp going?

17:42.237 --> 17:44.603
-Great. Couldn´t be better.
-Really?

17:45.040 --> 17:46.940
l happened to find a few of these...

17:47.009 --> 17:49.034
flying around Main Street.

17:50.579 --> 17:52.012
Mary Anne...

17:52.414 --> 17:55.315
l got the most outrageous outfit
for the concert.

17:57.452 --> 17:59.283
l´m not going to cry.

18:03.225 --> 18:04.954
l´ll be right back.

18:08.096 --> 18:11.759
Listen, you guys, we´ve been fighting
each other since the third grade...

18:11.833 --> 18:15.530
and now that we´re getting older,
don´t you think it´s time we stop?

18:15.604 --> 18:17.071
We´re having our annual BSC party...

18:17.139 --> 18:19.607
-tomorrow night at Miller´s Park at 8:00.
-What party?

18:19.674 --> 18:23.576
lf you could come,
it would be great, 8:00 sharp.

18:23.845 --> 18:25.437
Right, l´m sure.

18:26.815 --> 18:28.339
-What?
-l don´t know.

18:28.417 --> 18:31.284
-We don´t have anything to do tomorrow.
-Of course we do.

18:31.353 --> 18:34.049
lt´s Friday night.
We´ll be hanging out at Pizza Express.

18:34.122 --> 18:37.182
l think we should go.
Besides, they´re kind of cool.

18:38.293 --> 18:39.624
They´re not cool.

18:39.694 --> 18:42.561
We´re cool, and don´t you ever forget that.

18:43.031 --> 18:44.999
-What´s up?
-You´ll find out.

18:46.334 --> 18:49.462
Let´s see how cheese-ball
this baby-sitters´ party is gonna be.

18:49.538 --> 18:52.029
-They´re such girl scouts.
-Why are we here then?

18:52.107 --> 18:54.098
Logan Bruno will be here.

18:54.509 --> 18:56.443
What does he see in Mary Anne, anyway?

