27:39.500 --> 27:42.492
Yeah! No way is he gonna hit that ball!

27:42.570 --> 27:46.131
You got to strike out a couple times
before you hit a home run.

27:54.115 --> 27:56.709
He´s never gonna hit the ball!

27:57.151 --> 28:00.780
This is it. l can feel it.
l can see it in your elbow.

28:01.189 --> 28:03.817
He stinks! He´s the worst!

28:03.891 --> 28:05.756
He´s not gonna hit it!

28:13.868 --> 28:16.894
Mary here is on a time out
for sticking gum in Charlotte´s hair.

28:16.971 --> 28:18.165
Margie.

28:18.806 --> 28:21.297
-Margie, how old are you?
-Four-and-a-half.

28:21.376 --> 28:25.005
-You´re on a four-and-a-half minute time out.
-No, l´m two.

28:31.386 --> 28:33.980
-What do you think?
-l don´t really belong here.

28:34.055 --> 28:36.080
Please, you´ve got to come with me.

28:36.157 --> 28:38.591
Kristy, it isn´t like you´re six or something.

28:38.660 --> 28:42.619
l mean, you´re almost 13.
lt´s not like you need a chaperone.

28:44.532 --> 28:46.432
l don´t wanna go alone.

28:54.676 --> 28:58.168
Kristy, you´re gonna love this.
You too, Mary Anne, l hope.

28:58.246 --> 29:01.443
That´s okay. l don´t have to eat.
l could even leave.

29:01.516 --> 29:03.643
No. She´ll eat anything.

29:05.386 --> 29:08.014
Good, because my hotel
didn´t have a kitchen...

29:08.089 --> 29:10.956
and l wanted to make you
something really special.

29:11.592 --> 29:13.560
-So guess what it is.
-l don´t know.

29:13.628 --> 29:15.152
You don´t know?

29:18.433 --> 29:19.832
Mouse pancakes.

29:19.901 --> 29:22.961
Yeah, mouse pancakes.

29:23.471 --> 29:26.998
Wow, Dad. l mean Patrick.

29:29.077 --> 29:30.601
What´s in this?

29:30.678 --> 29:32.543
-Pancake mix.
-You´re a little rusty.

29:32.613 --> 29:34.604
When Kristy was little...

29:34.682 --> 29:37.947
the only way l could get her to eat
was to make her mouse pancakes.

29:38.019 --> 29:40.715
So we did every Sunday morning.
Right, pal?

29:41.022 --> 29:42.751
So when are you gonna call Mom?

29:42.824 --> 29:44.985
Soon. l´ve been really busy.

29:46.561 --> 29:49.223
Dad, a phone call
doesn´t take that much time.

29:51.065 --> 29:53.260
l´m gonna go to the bathroom.

29:58.005 --> 29:59.370
Where is it?

29:59.440 --> 30:03.342
Rest rooms. See that maple down there?
You take a left at the maple.

30:03.411 --> 30:05.345
Don´t worry, they´re clean.

30:11.486 --> 30:13.351
Your mom thinks l´m a loser.

30:13.855 --> 30:16.824
All right? So before l walk
into that mansion you live in...

30:16.891 --> 30:19.826
l gotta have a job, l gotta have a home...

30:20.194 --> 30:22.822
and a few things put together,
you know what l mean?

30:22.897 --> 30:26.697
Plus Chris Almond at the paper says
a couple days, a week tops.

30:28.703 --> 30:30.637
Think you can give me that?

30:30.805 --> 30:32.170
l guess so.

30:35.076 --> 30:36.168
Good.

30:37.311 --> 30:39.074
l got you something.

30:58.166 --> 30:59.360
Thanks!

31:02.370 --> 31:06.363
-What? You don´t like it? l can take it back.
-No, don´t do that.

31:07.375 --> 31:08.842
lt´s really nice...

31:09.410 --> 31:10.843
for a dress.

31:14.949 --> 31:16.576
Do you really like the dress?

31:16.651 --> 31:18.312
Yeah. lt´s great.

31:19.754 --> 31:21.722
Forgot why l got up.

31:23.991 --> 31:26.983
-Kristy, you have to tell your mom.
-l can´t. l promised.

31:27.061 --> 31:28.790
And you cannot tell anyone.

31:28.863 --> 31:31.627
But l tell Dawn everything,
and l tell Logan even more.

31:31.699 --> 31:34.600
You can´t, Mary Anne. Not this time. Swear.

31:35.002 --> 31:36.367
All right.

31:36.971 --> 31:40.168
-But who cares if he has a job yet or not?
-Him, l guess.

31:40.241 --> 31:43.574
Can you believe he gave me a dress?
What was l supposed to say?

31:43.644 --> 31:46.306
´´Sorry, l only wear dresses
at weddings and funerals´´?

31:46.380 --> 31:48.314
-He´d think l was crazy.
-You are.

31:48.382 --> 31:49.542
l win.

31:50.384 --> 31:52.716
Your mom looks just like Jo
in Little Women.

31:52.787 --> 31:55.153
-You think so?
-Yeah. You look like him.

31:55.223 --> 31:56.815
-l do?
-A little.

31:57.558 --> 32:00.891
-What if l talk about him in my sleep?
-l´m sleeping over, remember?

32:00.962 --> 32:04.022
lf you talk, l´ll stuff a pillow in your face.

32:09.136 --> 32:10.398
You okay?

32:10.471 --> 32:12.268
Kind of freaked out.

32:18.346 --> 32:21.372
Welcome to Punch and Judy Day!

32:21.616 --> 32:24.050
Look, Mary Anne. l didn´t say yes.

32:24.118 --> 32:26.882
-But you didn´t say no.
-But l didn´t say yes.

32:26.954 --> 32:29.354
l wasn´t gonna go with Cokie.

32:29.423 --> 32:31.687
Cross your heart and hope to die?

32:44.472 --> 32:46.633
Welcome to Sports Day.

32:46.707 --> 32:50.040
Remember, only do sports
in your sports group.

32:55.082 --> 32:57.880
Okay, you know
what you´re supposed to do.

32:58.419 --> 32:59.886
l´ll distract him.

33:06.360 --> 33:09.955
Logan, l like your jeans. Nice fit.

33:10.898 --> 33:12.126
Hi, Cokie.

33:13.234 --> 33:15.759
Cokie, how are you?

33:16.203 --> 33:18.433
Your skin looks a little dry.

33:19.674 --> 33:22.837
You´re trying to insult me. How hilarious.

33:29.717 --> 33:31.116
Nice muscle.

33:32.553 --> 33:35.351
Loved your little party in Miller´s Park.

33:40.561 --> 33:43.052
-We did it.
-Great! Did you pull the tab?

33:43.397 --> 33:45.365
We didn´t pull anything.

33:45.766 --> 33:48.257
You were supposed to pull, you freak!

33:51.205 --> 33:52.832
Look what we got!

33:52.907 --> 33:53.999
Cool!

34:14.195 --> 34:15.560
You brats!

34:16.797 --> 34:20.426
-Jackie, l gotta go, okay?
-What do you mean? We gotta practice.

34:20.501 --> 34:23.163
-Sorry, Jackie. How about tomorrow?
-l guess.

34:23.237 --> 34:24.864
-Mallory.
-Yeah?

34:25.272 --> 34:27.706
-Mallory, cover for me, okay? l gotta go.
-Why?

34:27.775 --> 34:30.175
l gotta leave early. So see you.

34:31.445 --> 34:34.437
l won´t miss the next one, Jackie.
Okay? Promise.

34:37.851 --> 34:39.217
l don´t believe this.

34:39.286 --> 34:41.083
-What in the--
-Who´s that man?

34:41.155 --> 34:42.621
This is too weird.

34:42.690 --> 34:44.783
Kristy has a boyfriend?

34:44.859 --> 34:47.987
-The world must be flat.
-Who´s the guy?

34:48.661 --> 34:50.186
-No one.
-No one?

34:50.431 --> 34:52.126
Who is he, Mary Anne?

34:52.199 --> 34:54.759
l can´t tell you. l promised.

34:55.469 --> 34:58.734
Since when did we start
keeping secrets, Mary Anne?

34:59.040 --> 35:00.132
Hello?

35:01.642 --> 35:04.873
l´m Emily Haberman.
l´m your neighbor. l live next door.

35:04.945 --> 35:07.812
Hi, Mrs. Haberman.
Sometimes l see you in your garden.

35:07.882 --> 35:10.908
A little while ago, l was nearly asphyxiated...

35:10.985 --> 35:15.046
by a smelly, stinking, disgusting projectile...

35:15.122 --> 35:17.420
and l, frankly, have had enough!

35:17.491 --> 35:20.016
-lt wasn´t us.
-We didn´t know.

35:20.094 --> 35:22.028
Would you happen to know...

35:22.096 --> 35:25.793
what little buzzy insects and small children
have in common?

35:26.167 --> 35:29.068
They both have the ability
to drive a human being...

35:29.136 --> 35:32.128
who is both larger and smarter...

35:32.206 --> 35:34.299
completely out of her mind.

35:35.176 --> 35:38.111
Now, you look like decent, sensible girls...

35:38.712 --> 35:41.374
so let´s just call this a warning, shall we?

35:41.449 --> 35:44.247
-But if there´s any more trouble--
-There won´t be.

35:44.318 --> 35:46.752
You make sure there isn´t,
because if there is...

35:46.821 --> 35:49.289
l shall be forced to call the city...

35:49.356 --> 35:52.325
and speak to them
about revoking your permit.

35:53.360 --> 35:56.124
-Permit?
-Yes. Permit.

35:56.831 --> 35:59.493
-She´s a hermit?
-lsn´t that some kind of animal?

35:59.567 --> 36:01.262
Permit, you idiots!

36:06.140 --> 36:08.233
Claudia, are you studying?

36:10.945 --> 36:14.472
l was so caught up with my dad,
l wasn´t being much of a club president...

36:14.548 --> 36:16.482
and Claud was going through it, too.

36:16.550 --> 36:20.008
Besides camp, she had summer school
and l hated to admit it...

36:20.087 --> 36:22.419
but she was doing
some of my camp work, too.

36:22.490 --> 36:24.924
But somehow, and l don´t know how...

36:24.992 --> 36:28.325
she managed to come up
with a really great plan for the BSC.

36:28.863 --> 36:32.128
l think l´m having my first brilliant idea.

36:33.434 --> 36:36.130
So what do you think?
lsn´t this a cool place?

36:38.239 --> 36:40.434
lt was built in 1 767.

36:40.508 --> 36:44.069
Then later, in the 1800s,
someone turned it into a greenhouse.

36:44.145 --> 36:46.306
Did we even have a country back then?

36:46.380 --> 36:48.871
No, but we had a lot of diphtheria.

36:51.886 --> 36:55.014
l´m writing a novel
about the first nurse in America.

36:55.089 --> 36:56.181
Okay.

36:57.057 --> 36:58.922
Let´s go in, you guys.

36:59.760 --> 37:00.988
We checked into it.

37:01.061 --> 37:04.997
