and toilet paper clean pretty well.

01:23:14.198 --> 01:23:15.961
This time we did all the grunt work.

01:23:16.034 --> 01:23:20.300
And with the help of the kids,
we got that place cleaned up in record time.

01:23:21.739 --> 01:23:24.833
And best of all,
Claud and l were friends again.

01:23:33.551 --> 01:23:35.246
l don´t believe this.

01:23:35.353 --> 01:23:38.652
They saw a problem,
and they worked hard to solve it.

01:23:38.756 --> 01:23:41.316
What are you saying?
Being good gets you somewhere?

01:23:41.392 --> 01:23:44.759
Being bad didn´t.
l mean, we wasted our whole summer.

01:23:45.396 --> 01:23:48.024
You didn´t waste it. You were with me.

01:23:48.566 --> 01:23:50.363
You got an education.

01:23:53.037 --> 01:23:54.095
Ready?

01:23:54.172 --> 01:23:57.903
The civic committee showed up.
Just our luck, right on time.

01:23:58.209 --> 01:23:59.540
Did they say anything?

01:23:59.610 --> 01:24:02.340
-You´ve shown a lot of civic pride.
-Yes.

01:24:02.647 --> 01:24:06.378
And we would love to grant your request
to use the structure.

01:24:06.784 --> 01:24:08.115
We´ve done it!

01:24:09.053 --> 01:24:11.453
But l´m afraid it´s not possible.

01:24:12.390 --> 01:24:15.359
-Why?
-You charge for your services, don´t you?

01:24:15.426 --> 01:24:16.552
Definitely.

01:24:16.627 --> 01:24:19.926
Then you consider yourself
more a business than a club.

01:24:20.031 --> 01:24:21.157
Absolutely.

01:24:21.332 --> 01:24:25.132
-And your business makes you money?
-What good business doesn´t?

01:24:25.203 --> 01:24:27.171
l believe we have a problem.

01:24:27.572 --> 01:24:30.905
Our charter states that any facility....

01:24:31.976 --> 01:24:34.638
Bird Face is on the committee? We´re dead.

01:24:35.346 --> 01:24:39.214
They wanted the place for their garden club,
and give us a commemorative plaque.

01:24:39.283 --> 01:24:41.114
Come off it, Harold.

01:24:41.719 --> 01:24:45.120
We´re not talking about
a multimillion-dollar corporation here.

01:24:45.189 --> 01:24:48.124
How much money
could their business possibly make?

01:24:48.259 --> 01:24:50.955
Our expenses ran a little away from us.

01:24:51.029 --> 01:24:54.430
l mean, between start-up costs,
freebies, camp supplies...

01:24:54.532 --> 01:24:58.161
the money to fix up this place
and miscellaneous expenses...

01:24:58.269 --> 01:24:59.759
our total profit...

01:24:59.904 --> 01:25:02.395
is $168.1 7.

01:25:03.474 --> 01:25:04.532
What?

01:25:05.910 --> 01:25:08.970
-That´s all?
-l can´t breathe. l have to go.

01:25:09.380 --> 01:25:11.211
They´re dropping like flies.

01:25:11.282 --> 01:25:13.580
lf memory serves me correctly...

01:25:13.818 --> 01:25:16.810
our committee bylaws state
that any company...

01:25:16.888 --> 01:25:21.655
must show a profit of $1,500 a year
to qualify as a viable business.

01:25:21.959 --> 01:25:24.519
These girls are obviously nowhere near that.

01:25:24.629 --> 01:25:28.759
Therefore, l see no reason
why they can´t use this as their office.

01:25:29.100 --> 01:25:32.194
Fine. Do whatever you want, Emily.
l don´t care.

01:25:34.605 --> 01:25:36.197
l need some air.

01:25:41.712 --> 01:25:45.546
l don´t think they´re quite used
to this tropical environment.

01:25:45.650 --> 01:25:47.982
Reminds me of my days in Calcutta.

01:25:49.754 --> 01:25:52.450
ls it always gonna be this hot in here?

01:25:55.193 --> 01:25:57.684
lt was turning into an amazing day.

01:25:57.962 --> 01:25:59.827
We got the greenhouse.

01:26:01.165 --> 01:26:03.395
Jackie hit his first home run.

01:26:22.687 --> 01:26:24.018
Cokie got it so bad...

01:26:24.088 --> 01:26:27.888
l knew it was the last time the BSC
would ever hear from Cokie Mason.

01:26:27.959 --> 01:26:29.790
For this summer, anyway.

01:26:29.861 --> 01:26:31.522
All right, Jackie!

01:26:42.573 --> 01:26:44.234
Way to go, Jackie!

01:26:50.681 --> 01:26:53.479
Will you go to the movies with me tonight?

01:26:54.085 --> 01:26:55.609
Alan, get real.

01:27:00.324 --> 01:27:01.382
l am.

01:27:01.626 --> 01:27:04.356
l´ve been trying to ask you out all summer.

01:27:06.998 --> 01:27:08.192
Really?

01:27:09.567 --> 01:27:10.659
Yeah.

01:27:16.974 --> 01:27:18.066
Okay.

01:27:31.889 --> 01:27:33.550
Are you lovebirds yet?

01:27:34.358 --> 01:27:37.088
When l got home,
there was another letter from my dad.

01:27:37.161 --> 01:27:41.825
l couldn´t believe l heard from him so soon.
lt used to be years between letters.

01:27:41.899 --> 01:27:43.389
Now it´s days.

01:27:45.570 --> 01:27:48.698
$168.1 7.

01:27:48.773 --> 01:27:50.297
We had a lot of overhead.

01:27:50.374 --> 01:27:52.934
Most businesses
don´t even survive their first year.

01:27:53.010 --> 01:27:55.103
We had to work out all the kinks.

01:27:55.179 --> 01:27:57.170
Are we taking the bed, Claudia?

01:27:57.248 --> 01:27:59.808
-We can´t take my furniture.
-What will we sit on?

01:27:59.884 --> 01:28:01.351
Can we take the rug?

01:28:01.419 --> 01:28:03.887
-l´m gonna miss it here.
-Me, too.

01:28:04.155 --> 01:28:07.022
-Where it all began. Right, Claud?
-Right.

01:28:07.091 --> 01:28:09.321
Can you get the licorice
from my nightstand?

01:28:09.393 --> 01:28:11.258
l don´t want to forget it.

01:28:12.964 --> 01:28:16.661
We spent some of the best years
of our lives in this place.

01:28:20.771 --> 01:28:23.001
lt´s so nice and cool in here.

01:28:35.386 --> 01:28:36.648
lt´s almost gone.

01:28:36.787 --> 01:28:38.618
-What?
-Summer.

01:28:46.264 --> 01:28:48.391
-Hi, Mrs. Haberman!
-Hello, Dawn.

01:28:48.733 --> 01:28:50.496
l´m sorry to bother you, but....

01:28:50.568 --> 01:28:53.435
The more we thought about it,
Claud´s room really was home.

01:28:53.504 --> 01:28:56.029
And Mrs. Haberman
had really come through for us.

01:28:56.107 --> 01:28:58.541
So, we figured
after what we´d put her through...

01:28:58.609 --> 01:29:01.578
the least we could do
was give her the greenhouse.

01:29:14.525 --> 01:29:16.584
lt´s all yours, Mrs. Haberman.

01:29:16.794 --> 01:29:18.887
-What do you mean?
-Come on.

01:29:21.299 --> 01:29:23.062
We thought you could use it.

01:29:23.134 --> 01:29:25.830
Might help you grow
all your flowers and stuff.

01:29:25.903 --> 01:29:29.600
We asked the nursery for whatever
might attract hummingbirds and butterflies.

01:29:29.674 --> 01:29:31.505
The sunflowers were my idea.

01:29:35.579 --> 01:29:38.673
l guess Stoneybrook could use
a nature conservancy.

01:29:42.987 --> 01:29:46.946
You guys are gonna end up
with your names on a plaque after all.

01:29:48.959 --> 01:29:51.189
Okay, we´ll put those there.

01:29:51.262 --> 01:29:54.129
All right, everybody. Come on. Group shot.

01:29:55.299 --> 01:29:58.791
After buying Mrs. Haberman plants
and getting our answering machine...

01:29:58.869 --> 01:30:00.928
all we were left with was $18.

01:30:01.505 --> 01:30:04.872
So we splurged and blew the whole thing
on an extra-large pizza...

01:30:04.942 --> 01:30:07.934
double cheese, double sauce,
double anchovies.

01:30:08.446 --> 01:30:11.438
Dawn had a tricolore salad, whatever that is.

01:30:11.849 --> 01:30:15.910
